  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing the Capacity of Jordan&#x2019;s Border Authorities to Respond to COVID-19 and Mitigate Its Socioeconomic Impact</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Responding to the COVID-19 pandemic and its repercussions, IOM will work to enhance the capacity of the Jordanian Government to limit the spread of COVID-19 and the scope of the public health crisis, while also preventing the interruption of supply chains that border closures would cause, thereby mitigating the pandemic&#x2019;s socioeconomic impact on Jordan. This will be achieved by supporting Border Authorities with appropriate infrastructure and equipment, including personal protective equipment, while also training staff present at points of entry to screen, detect and safely handle, isolate, and refer suspected cases of COVID-19 and other communicable diseases, in line with IOM&#x2019;s Health Border and Mobility Management (HBMM) framework.</narrative>
  </description>
